[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Mena-asia_default_banner.jpg"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Image:Bihoro_Pass.JPG"],["thumb"],["240px"],["Bihoro Pass and Highway 243"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Bihoro"]}," (美幌, ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.ohotuku26.or.jp\/bihoro\/"]},") is an insufferably obscure farming town in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okhotsk (subprefecture)"],["Okhotsk"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hokkaido"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Japan"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\nBihoro is a 20-minute bus ride away from Memanbetsu Airport (¥340).\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nBihoro is on the ",{"type":"'''","value":["JR Sekihoku Line"]}," (石北本線) from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Asahikawa"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abashiri"]]},".\n\nThe ",{"type":"'''","value":["Okhotsk"]}," limited express runs to Bihoro from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sapporo"]]}," in about 5 hours at a cost of ¥9430.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By road"]},"\nBihoro is a major road junction and highways lead from here to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abashiri"]]}," on the northern coast, to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Teshikaga"]]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Akan National Park"]]},") and to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Asahikawa"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sounkyo Onsen"]]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Daisetsuzan National Park"]]},").  Buses run along most roads but only very intermittently.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Bihoro Pass"],["alt=美幌峠 Bihoro-tōge"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions=On Highway 243 between Bihoro and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Teshikaga"]]},"."],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=This is Bihoro's sole claim to fame, affording views over Lake Kussharo in the nearby ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Akan National Park"]]},".  The pass was also canonized in the eponymous ",{"type":"''","value":["enka"]}," (Japanese folk song), which now plays on repeat in the small service area near the pass."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Bihoro Agricultural Museum"],["alt=星美幌農業館 Bihoro-nōgyōkan"],["url=http:\/\/www.ohotuku26.or.jp\/bihoro\/bibot\/ex_e\/index_e.html"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours=9AM-5PM daily"],["price=¥300"],["content= With exhibits like \"Modern Agricultural Machines\" and \"Let's Play With BIBOT\", this is best reserved for those ",{"type":"''","value":["really"]}," rainy days."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["do"],["name=Tōge-no-Yu Bihoro"],["alt=峠の湯びほろ"],["url=http:\/\/www.ohotuku26.or.jp\/bihoro\/telguide\/458.html"],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=Entry ¥500, entry and shuttle ¥900"],["content=The inevitable hot spring, but a fairly modern and pleasant operation — and yes, that does mean \"Pass Hot Water Bihoro\"."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Buy"]},"\nBihoro's speciality is ",{"type":"''","value":["kumazasa-cha"]}," (熊笹茶), a type of herbal tea made from the ",{"type":"''","value":["kumazasa"]}," (lit. \"bear grass\") leaf that grows abundantly in this harsh climate.  Steeply priced at ¥840 per bag, but worth a try.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name=Gurutto Panorama Bihoro"],["alt=ぐるっとパノラマ美幌峠"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=The fancy name of the highway service area at Bihoro Pass ... but in addition to the souvenir and fried-everything-on-a-stick vendors downstairs, there's a decent restaurant upstairs which serves ",{"type":"''","value":["kumazasa"]}," tea along with your meal."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Sleep"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["sleep"],["name=Minshuku Tarō-an"],["alt=民宿太郎庵"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions=Right across the street from the JR station"],["phone = +81 1527-3-4310"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price=Room with 2 meals ¥5000"],["checkin="],["checkout="],["content=A tiny minshuku (capacity 7 people)."]]}]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Connect"]},"\nThe small tourism office in the train station will be overjoyed at seeing an actual tourist.  They can also book accommodation for you.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Akan National Park"]]}," — Just across the Bihoro Pass are a number of nice sights."]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["routebox"],["image1=JR Sekihoku icon.png"],["imagesize1=100"],["directionl1=W"],["majorl1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Asahikawa"]]}],["minorl1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kitami"]]}],["directionr1=E"],["majorr1=",{"type":"[[","value":[["Abashiri"]]}],["minorr1="]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Okhotsk (subprefecture)"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["Outlinecity"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["WikiPedia:Bihoro, Abashiri, Hokkaido"]]},{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["43.823611111111"],["144.10722222222"]]}]